properties.areaDesc: South Central Oregon Coast; Curry County Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Warning issued January 10 at 11:40AM PST until January 11 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Medford OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerously large breaking waves of 28 to 32 feet.

* WHERE...South Central Oregon Coast and Curry County Coast.
Highest surf is expected on west and northwest facing beaches.

* WHEN...From 10 PM Friday to 10 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Extremely large breaking waves will create very
hazardous conditions along beaches and area shorelines. Waves
will inundate beaches and surge into normally dry areas.
Infrastructure damage and significant beach erosion can be
expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Very high tides late Saturday morning to
early afternoon will result in even higher wave runup.

* View the hazard area in detail at
https://www.wrh.noaa.gov/mfr/HAZARD
properties.instruction:
Beaches and coastlines will become hazardous due to very large
and life-threatening surf conditions. Stay off of beaches, rocks,
jetties,piers, and other waterside infrastructure.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 PM PST SATURDAY
